      "collision": false,
      "interactable": {
        "type": "dialogue",
        "hoverText": "☉ Speak to the Archivist",
        "requires": "has_credential",
        "requiresText": "The Archivist's stone nostrils flare. It sniffs the air and turns away. It seems to require some kind of... olfactory credential.",
        "dialogue": {
          "nodes": [
            {
              "speaker": "T H E   A R C H I V I S T",
              "text": "You bring the correct scent... yes. I file all records by S M E L L. You smell like the last petitioner. And the one before that."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "T H E   A R C H I V I S T",
              "text": "You want the Word for the Sealed Arch? I catalogued it once... under G R E E N   M I N E R A L S. Or was it 'things that are not plants'? The categories overlap."
            },
            {
              "speaker": "T H E   A R C H I V I S T",
              "text": "I cannot remember the exact Word. But I remember it was the name of a S T O N E — the green one. Check the Obelisk. I filed the mineral registry there. Under 'tall things.'"
            },
            {
              "speaker": "T H E   A R C H I V I S T",
              "text": "The code beyond the Arch is expired. But we have not updated the system. This is... A D V A N T A G E O U S."
            }
          ]
        },
        "onComplete": {
